	<li class="span6">
		<h2>The Christmas Demo EP! <small>FOR MOM, DAD & ANTHONY</small></h2>
		<p>For the family who has been so supportive of my creative endeavors over the years, but only gets to see a sliver of them because I'm a perfectionist.  I've tried to throw a little bit of that out the window in putting this album together, so expect the mic to peak, and the guitar to fumble: <b>(a)</b> because I wouldn't have gotten it done otherwise <b>(b)</b> with the exception of the first track for which I don't really know what the point is, the point is mostly the songwriting, not the production/performance <b>(c)</b> you're my parents/brother and you love me. - r</p>

		<h4>TRACKLISTING<small> click titles for lyrics</small></H4>
		<p>1. <b><a href="#Blue_River">Blue River</a></b> (Mitchell/Hayes/Johnson) <b>1:57</b> <i>Specially written/adapted for this EP, consider it the digital musical equivalent of a macaroni photo frame.</i></p>
		<p>2. <b><a href="#Sweet_Something">Sweet Something</b></a> (Cima) <b>2:59</b> <i>Chords inspired by a Rolling Stones song in a somber montage a James Bond movie in a dream, probably the first thing I will play on Sal's telecaster.</i></p>
		<p>3. <b><a href="#Runaway_Heart">Runaway Heart</a></b> (Cima) <b>3:07</b> <i>A Hank-Williams-y kind of thing, with mixed metaphors and mixed guitar-playing.  The production quality is more forgivable if you pretend I am indigenous to somewhere and have hookworm.</i></p>
		<p>4. <b><a href="#Setting_Sun">House of My Setting Sun</a></b> (Cima) <b>2:33</b> <i>I spent a while recording it on multiple tracks only to find that I liked the extra-early version I played into my iPhone way better than anyting else, why it's in mp4.</i></p>

		
	</li>

        <li class="span4">
