	<section id="Setting_Sun">

		<br/><br/><br/>

		<h3>House of My Setting Sun</h3>

		<p>There's a house down in Los Angeles<br/>
		I call my setting sun<br/>
		Oblivion waits there for me<br/>
		At the hands of a lovely one</p>

		<p>She's got fingers like piano keys<br/>
		And hair as fair as August<br/>
		A hot white bullet she's promised me<br/>
		And her word I trust</p>

		<p>Her lover was a movies man<br/>
		Eyes like a silver screen<br/>
		He swore he'd see her through the end<br/>
		But then those eyes caught me</p>

		<p>He let me play the role<br/>
		Of a Juliet in flight<br/>
		He peered into my soul<br/>
		And then turned out the light</p>

		<p>And now we live in Burlingame<br/>
		Two bedroom tan and beige<br/>
		And every day here is the same<br/>
		His silver's all gone grey</p>

		<p>There's an old house in Los Angeles<br/>
		I call my Brigadoon<br/>
		A crimson climax cries for me<br/>
		I might just answer soon</p>

		<br/><br/><br/>

	</section>



	

